  "technicalDetails": "<p>Features:</p><ul><li> Easy to use</li><li> Very versatile</li><li> Makes text render actor animation and layout trivial!</li></ul><p>Number of Blueprints: 3 blueprints &#43; 1 function library (blueprints are two page types, and the animator blueprint)</p><p>&#43; 5 Structs for animation data &#43; 1 Enum for color fade speeds</p><p>Input: Mouse, Keyboard, Gamepad</p><p>Network Replicated: No</p><p>Supported Development Platforms:</p><p>Windows: Yes</p><p>Mac: Yes</p><p>Documentation: <a href=\"https://youtu.be/DE-tqct3gMg\" rel=\"nofollow\">Page Maker Demo</a></p><p>BP_TextAnimator acts like a function. Feed it a text actor, and fill in the animation info struct pin. IF you want to use the animation functions manually, to create custom sequences for example, simply deactivate all animations when spawning the TextAnimator. Then you can use it to call whichever animation you want manually.</p>",
